Product: Clinora

Version: 1.0

Document Type: Database Design & Entity Relationship Document (ERD)

Audience: Backend Developers, Database Engineers, Architects, QA, DevOps

1. Purpose

This document defines the logical database design for the Clinora platform.

It describes the core entities, relationships, database rules, naming conventions, indexing strategy, audit requirements, and multi-tenant design.

This document acts as the single source of truth for backend development and database implementation.

2. Database Technology
Component	Technology
Database	PostgreSQL
ORM	Spring Data JPA / Hibernate
Migration	Flyway
UUID	UUID Primary Keys
Soft Delete	Supported
Audit	Created/Updated timestamps
3. Design Principles

Every table should follow these standards:

UUID primary keys
Audit fields
Tenant isolation
Soft delete support
Foreign key relationships
Optimized indexes
Normalized schema (avoid unnecessary duplication)
