17. Multi-Tenant Rule

Every business table includes:

clinic_id

Every query automatically filters using:

WHERE clinic_id = ?

No cross-clinic access is permitted.

18. Audit Columns

Every table contains:

created_by

created_at

updated_by

updated_at

Optional

deleted_at

deleted_by
19. Index Strategy

Indexes should exist for:

clinic_id

patient_id

doctor_id

appointment_date

payment_status

email

mobile

invoice_number

transaction_id

Composite indexes:

(clinic_id, appointment_date)

(clinic_id, doctor_id)

(clinic_id, patient_id)
20. Database Constraints

Examples:

Unique email per clinic
Unique mobile per clinic
Unique patient number per clinic
Unique invoice number per clinic
Prevent duplicate active appointments for the same doctor and time slot
Foreign keys enforce data integrity
21. Future Tables

Future releases may add:

Insurance Claims
Inventory
Pharmacy
CRM
Marketing Campaigns
AI Conversation History
Telemedicine Sessions
Multi-Branch Support
22. Migration Strategy

All schema changes must be managed using Flyway.

Example:

V1__Create_Clinic.sql
V2__Create_User.sql
V3__Create_Patient.sql
V4__Create_Doctor.sql
...

This ensures every environment (development, QA, production) stays synchronized.

23. Naming Standards

Tables

Lowercase
Plural names
Snake case

Example:

patients
appointments
lab_reports

Columns

first_name
appointment_date
created_at

Primary Keys

id

Foreign Keys

patient_id
doctor_id
clinic_id
24. Document Summary

This document defines the complete logical data model for Clinora. It provides the foundation for backend implementation, API development, reporting, analytics, and future scalability while maintaining tenant isolation and data integrity.
